            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--frag; dated by priests, records a proxeny of Sosis, granted by the koinon of the Muse (on these, cf. Lintott (1993), 178 with refs.). Manganaro and Moretti propose various restorations; stone was lost already in time of Orsi, but rediscovered by Manni Piraino. Cf. the several others of this type, five in all, discussed together by Manganaro 1963 (IG 14.12 and 13, and two publ. by Gentili, ASS 7 (1961), p.10ff. (BE 1971 is notice of rediscovery by Manni-Piraino; BE 1964 is discussion of Moretti and Manganaro). Manganaro 1977 disagrees with M-P's restorations. He also thinks the koinon could go back to Hieron II on a Ptolemaic model.--></p>
            </div>
